body:
Is there any way to send the SMS verification code?

I tried the following code:
```php
		public function sendCode($number)
		{
			$countryCode = substr($number, 0, 2);
			$subNumber=substr($number, 2);
			
			$url = "https://r.whatsapp.net/v1/code.php?cc=".$countryCode."&in=".$subNumber."&to=".$number."&lc=DE&lg=de&mcc=000&mnc=000&method=sms";
			
			$ch = curl_init();
			curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_URL, $url);
			curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, 1);
			curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_USERAGENT, "User-Agent:WhatsApp/2.8.4 iPhone_OS/5.1.1 Device/Unknown_(iPhone4,1)");
			
			curl_exec($ch);
			curl_close($ch);
		}
```

I always get a return containing `fail-too-many` as errorcode, even after disabling the app on my phone.
I was able to get WhatsApp to send me a new code using a different phone, even with WhatsApp still running on my phone, so it shouldn't really matter.

Trying to send the request without a valid WhatsApp useragent returns a "success-sent" (without actually sending the code).
